            <div class="col-md-9 col-md-pull-3" role="main">
                <section id="cdn_home" class="group">
                    <h1>Overview</h1>
                    <p>
                        The ManiaCDN is a set of mirrors provided by the community in order to provide a stable cluster of servers to provide static content for game content
                    </p>

                    <h3>Content</h3>
                    <p>
                        Contents of the CDN is managed by validated authors. They can update their files and it will be available within 12 hours (but mostly 6 hours) on the whole network.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        You can apply as a content provider by clicking the Distribute my Content button. You can also read more information about the process of checking and rules.
                    </p>
                    <a href="#cdn_request" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm">Distribute my Content</a>

                    <h3>Management</h3>
                    <p>
                        Servers are automaticly being updated with the newest files distributed over the network.
                        We also check every so often if the servers are still updating and will directly suspend it when it's providing old content.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        New servers are always welcome! Please click on the button Donate my Server to see how you can donate to the CDN.
                    </p>
                    <a href="#cdn_request" class="btn btn-success btn-sm">Donate my Server</a>
                </section>

                <section id="cdn_status" class="group">
                    <h1>Status</h1>
                    <p>The actual status of the ManiaCDN network:</p>

                    <p>Online mirrors: {{mirrorsOnline}}</p>

                </section>

                <section id="cdn_mirrors" class="group">
                    <h1>Mirrors</h1>
                    <p>List with mirrors and the update time</p>

                    <table class="table table-hover table-responsive">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>IP</th>
                                <th>Loc.</th>
                                <th>Active</th>
                                <th>Status</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                        {{#each mirrors}}
                            {{#if active}}
                                <tr class="">
                            {{else}}
                                <tr class="active">
                            {{/if}}
                                <td>
                                    <code>
                                        {{ip4}}{{ip6}}
                                    </code>
                                </td>

                                <td>
                                    {{countrycode}}
                                </td>

                                <td>
                                    {{#if active}}
                                        <label class="label label-success">
                                            Active
                                        </label>
                                    {{else}}
                                        <label class="label label-warning">
                                            Inactive
                                        </label>
                                    {{/if}}
                                </td>

                                <td>
                                    <div class="server-status" data-status="{{status}}"></div>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                        {{/each}}
                        </tbody>
                    </table>

                </section>

                <section id="cdn_request" class="group">
                    <h1>Get involved</h1>
                    <p class="lead">
                        If you want to distribute or mirror the content. Please visit our IRC channel #mp-cdn on QuakeNet, or send an PM to 'toffe' or 'askuri' on the ManiaPlanet forum.
                    </p>
                </section>


                <section id="cdn_about" class="group">
                    <h1>About the CDN</h1>
                    <p>
                        We are Askuri and Toffe. Together we lead this project to the best way you could think. We think we should
                        be active for a lifetime! <br>
                        <span class="text-muted">Bit sarcasm, but ye, as we get users that rely on us we need to stay up! We take this really serious!</span>.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        Toffe is working on the technical dns stuff and the website.<br>
                        Askuri is the one that maintains the master repo and will constant work on the content itself.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        We are working with Open Source at most of the mirros, atleast our master repo and even this site and checking logic is open sourced! (by ourself!).<br>
                        <a href="https://github.com/ManiaCDN" target="_blank" class="btn btn-sm btn-info">GitHub</a>
                    </p>
                    </section>

                <section id="cdn_abuse" class="group">
                    <h1>Abuse & Security</h1>
                    <p>
                        We want to give our users a safe and abuse-free content. And we are open to any takedown, security and other important reports!
                    </p>

                    <div id="cdn_abuse_security" class="subgroup">
                        <h2>Security</h2>
                        <p>
                            We take security pretty high. We would really like to get security reports or mirror abuse reports to make the network as secure as possible!
                        </p>

                        <div class="alert alert-warning">
                            <p>You can send security reports on security[AT]maniacdn.net</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="alert alert-info">
                            <p>If you would like to encrypt or sign your message, please use the GPG key provided here by <a href="http://about.maniacdn.net/gpg.txt">clicking here.</a></p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div id="cdn_abuse_takedown" class="subgroup">
                        <h2>DCMA Takedown</h2>
                        <p>
                            We will only serve non-copyright material. But when we do, we are open to take the file away!<br>
                            Please send us a email on dcma[AT]maniacdn.net with the DCMA takedown request.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </section>

